        "title": "config: add Nacos config source (file/nacos abstraction, reload subscribe, NACOS_NAMESPACE)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** Need optional config source from Nacos so gateway can load config from Nacos in memory with push-based updates and hot reload, without writing to pod filesystem.\n- **Why it matters:** Enables K8s/centralized config via Nacos; file source keeps current behavior.\n- **What changed:** Config source abstraction (file | nacos), file adapter, Nacos client (Open API + long-poll), snapshot-from-raw, resolve from env; gateway reloader supports `watchPath` or `subscribe`; config/io and server integrate source (readSnapshot/readConfigFileSnapshotForWrite/writeConfigFile with validation for Nacos path); optional `NACOS_NAMESPACE` (tenant) wired and documented.\n- **What did NOT change:** No Nacos SDK dependency; config parsing/validation pipeline shared; file path behavior unchanged.\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Feature\n- [x] Docs\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\n- [x] API / contracts\n\n## Linked Issue/PR\n\n- Implementation plan: `docs/plans/2026-03-18-nacos-config-source.md`\n\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\n\n- New env: `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_SOURCE=nacos`, `NACOS_SERVER_ADDR`, `NACOS_DATA_ID`, optional `NACOS_GROUP`, `NACOS_NAMESPACE`. When set, gateway loads config from Nacos; config write (RPC/CLI) updates in-memory snapshot only; hot reload driven by Nacos long-poll.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions/capabilities? No (optional, opt-in via env).\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? No.\n- New/changed network calls? Yes — Nacos HTTP (get config + long-poll) when Nacos source enabled.\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? No.\n- Data access scope changed? No.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\n- Backward compatible? Yes.\n- Config/env changes? New optional env vars only when using Nacos.\n- Migration needed? No.\n",
